                    </div>
                    <span>As an occasional Unix system administrator, I find that this is the book that I turn to the most. It is also quite readable and can be read front-to-back. However, Unix administration is a large enough topic that you should also get Essential System Administration by Aeleen Frisch (O'Reilly). There are some areas that this book covers more thoroughly, and some where Essential System Administration has the advantage. So get both.</span>
                  
              
